But it's definitely something that changes the air and I'm going to miss that greatly.

624
01:36:54,993 --> 01:36:58,235
I am still probably going to call you every time I'm like, how did we get where we are today?

625
01:36:58,255 --> 01:37:02,338
Because most of us now will not actually have answers to that question.

626
01:37:03,038 --> 01:37:08,162
And as Beth Fuller mentioned, it was before the internet and all that other stuff.

627
01:37:08,202 --> 01:37:10,383
So we can't just Google, how did we get here?

628
01:37:11,384 --> 01:37:20,890
So thank you so much for providing just that context and history and calmness and the room to feel so welcome.

629
01:37:23,262 --> 01:37:25,044
So this one isn't as wordy.

630
01:37:25,484 --> 01:37:30,610
This is from representative Catherine Clark, who was also a school committee member.

631
01:37:31,511 --> 01:37:38,257
I do love to remind everybody of people who have gone into other offices who were school committee members.

632
01:37:39,599 --> 01:37:45,065
The first time I met Catherine was at the high school for a run, I forget which run,

633
01:37:46,265 --> 01:37:58,869
And one of the first things she said was, was the hardest job ever and that is sort of a theme from anybody who's in a different elected office now, they say that the school committee was the hardest job they ever had in politics.

634
01:38:01,883 --> 01:38:07,086
I mean, I don't have context to say whether that's true, but it seems pretty good, like a good assessment.

635
01:38:07,606 --> 01:38:19,653
So this is a certificate of special congressional recognition presented to Paula Vander Kloot in recognition of outstanding and invaluable service to the community, signed today by Catherine M. Clark, member of Congress.

636
01:38:31,752 --> 01:38:32,513
Thank you.

637
01:38:32,593 --> 01:38:41,748
So I would now like to invite member of the storm forward to make some remarks and to present a citation from our own governor Baker.

638
01:38:51,951 --> 01:38:56,533
I just asked Jenny to Google if Governor Baker was on the school committee, because I think he was.

639
01:38:56,593 --> 01:38:57,173
So you're right.

640
01:38:57,233 --> 01:39:03,456
Paulette, you can be governor next.

641
01:39:03,816 --> 01:39:07,058
So this is from Governor Baker and Lieutenant Governor Perito.

642
01:39:07,998 --> 01:39:08,699
in its form.

643
01:39:08,899 --> 01:39:25,578
On behalf of the citizens of the Commonwealth of Massachusetts, I am pleased to confer upon you this Governor's citation and recognition of your 32 years of dedicated service as a member of the Medford School Committee to Paulette Van de Kloet the 20th day of December in the year 2021.

644
01:39:26,620 --> 01:39:28,001
I do just want to briefly say

645
01:39:28,802 --> 01:39:31,785
that I've appreciated so much working with you for these past six years.

646
01:39:31,805 --> 01:39:36,710
Honestly, it's incredible the service you've given to the city of Medford.

647
01:39:36,730 --> 01:39:42,255
I don't think anyone else in the city has given 32 years of their life or Bob's life.

648
01:39:46,420 --> 01:39:49,543
So I thank you and I look forward to having a drink with you after this.

649
01:39:57,696 --> 01:39:59,078
Thank you, Member Winslow.

650
01:39:59,898 --> 01:40:01,520
I'd like to invite Member Kretz up.

651
01:40:01,580 --> 01:40:06,266
She's going to present some remarks and a citation from Senator Markey.

652
01:40:20,753 --> 01:40:24,715
I just want to thank you for your 32 years of service and your friendship.

653
01:40:25,796 --> 01:40:28,758
Just like everybody said here tonight, it's just incredible.

654
01:40:29,559 --> 01:40:36,223
Your knowledge, your kindness, you know, we can call you, text you with any questions.

655
01:40:36,344 --> 01:40:37,925
You have a remarkable memory.

656
01:40:38,485 --> 01:40:40,266
you seem to remember everything.

657
01:40:40,286 --> 01:40:49,311
I don't know how you do it and I'm so glad you know my son got to know you with the volunteer program and you know you were a great mentor.

658
01:40:49,371 --> 01:41:07,182
He just loves volunteering and I'm so glad that he started with that program and it got him into a schedule and it just seems that everything you do it's just it's just wonderful and incredible and I'm so happy for you for your retirement to spend time with your grandchildren and your family and just to have

659
01:41:07,622 --> 01:41:08,402
more free time.

660
01:41:08,802 --> 01:41:11,343
You really deserve it, and I'm really happy for you.

661
01:41:11,764 --> 01:41:15,285
And I will miss you, and I'll probably reach out to you.

662
01:41:15,765 --> 01:41:19,166
So I have a citation, and I'll read it now.

663
01:41:20,267 --> 01:41:34,252
This is a certificate of special congressional recognition presented to Paulette Vanderkoot for her 32 years exemplary as member of Memphis School Committee in recognition of outstanding and invaluable service to the community.

664
01:41:34,752 --> 01:41:36,953
Signed by Senator Ed Mackey.

665
01:41:53,692 --> 01:41:54,893
I forgot my own remarks.

666
01:41:55,453 --> 01:41:59,576
So I two years ago when I was out campaigning I knocked on a woman's door.

667
01:42:10,482 --> 01:42:13,984
And we had a like 20 minute long conversation at her door.

668
01:42:14,605 --> 01:42:18,207
And I think she said that her kids went to school with Paulette's kids.

669
01:42:19,008 --> 01:42:21,249
And she said, do you know Paulette?

670
01:42:21,289 --> 01:42:23,110
And I said, why, yes, I do.

671
01:42:23,611 --> 01:42:29,374
We had worked on the superintendent search committee together that ultimately hired you, superintendent.

672
01:42:29,394 --> 01:42:30,255
Good job, good job.

673
01:42:33,759 --> 01:42:38,543
And also, we had worked on a number of things together when I was a parent.

674
01:42:39,143 --> 01:42:45,668
And this woman said, well, you know, before Paulette, parents weren't members of the school committee.

675
01:42:45,688 --> 01:42:47,970
And I said, really?

676
01:42:47,990 --> 01:42:48,570
OK.

677
01:42:48,670 --> 01:42:52,894
And I didn't know, but I was like, and she said, but Paulette is the one that changed that.

678
01:42:52,974 --> 01:42:56,036
Paulette is the reason why there are parents on the school committee today.

679
01:42:56,056 --> 01:42:57,257
So thank you.

680
01:43:04,337 --> 01:43:05,098
and you will be missed.

681
01:43:07,059 --> 01:43:08,040
Thank you.

682
01:43:08,960 --> 01:43:14,844
So I almost want to do a drum roll because, uh, yes, yes, yes, yes.

683
01:43:15,385 --> 01:43:20,008
We're going to have take the podium right now.

684
01:43:20,368 --> 01:43:26,132
And, um, we have some special things to present governor Paulette.

685
01:43:29,011 --> 01:43:30,512
whatever you choose in your retirement.

686
01:43:31,732 --> 01:43:44,998
I'm going to be brief as well but I just want to say I've always respected you as a counselor when you were a school committee member but and I know you were thinking should you run the last time and I just want to

687
01:43:45,858 --> 01:43:48,200
from the bottom of my heart, thank you for doing so.

688
01:43:49,160 --> 01:43:53,203
These last two years have been extremely difficult for all of us.

689
01:43:53,764 --> 01:44:09,395
Myself never have served in the school committee, a couple others that were very recent and you helped lead the committee through the toughest two years that I've ever been in politics and probably in your 32 years as well.

690
01:44:10,176 --> 01:44:14,459
There were nights where we would have eight hour meetings and I'd say, I need to come in and sit in

691
01:44:15,400 --> 01:44:26,588
say something and say the right thing and you would swoop in and just calmly and rationally solve what we needed to be solved at that moment.

692
01:44:26,748 --> 01:44:33,013
Or I would be home racking my brain on something school related and I would look at my phone and you'd be calling.

693
01:44:33,073 --> 01:44:39,118
It's almost like you knew when you needed to reach out to brainstorm or review something so we could try to

694
01:44:40,593 --> 01:44:41,194
make it better.

695
01:44:41,714 --> 01:44:44,096
And it's really helped me the last two years.

696
01:44:44,156 --> 01:44:51,941
I look up to you as a friend, as a colleague, and I just thank you for all you have done for all of our kids.

697
01:44:52,761 --> 01:44:53,902
We really appreciate it.

698
01:44:53,942 --> 01:44:56,204
I wish you the best of luck in your retirement.

699
01:44:56,864 --> 01:44:57,625
Congratulations.

700
01:45:04,729 --> 01:45:16,399
On behalf of the administration, the entire Medford School, public school community, we have the honor of presenting this final gift, which has an inscription here.

701
01:45:18,160 --> 01:45:19,221
Right, Dr. Cushing?

702
01:45:19,461 --> 01:45:20,422
It's okay, it's okay.

703
01:45:22,704 --> 01:45:25,687
Oh, you want me to read it?

704
01:45:25,827 --> 01:45:27,348
Paulette Van Der Koeuw.

705
01:45:27,968 --> 01:45:28,529
Given who?

706
01:45:28,549 --> 01:45:29,290
No, I'm just kidding.

707
01:45:33,099 --> 01:45:36,503
gratitude for 32 years of service to the method public schools.

708
01:46:01,017 --> 01:46:07,381
So, member Van Der Kroot, you would put in a special request.

709
01:46:08,442 --> 01:46:17,667
And so that was the big, big one for you that you can read stories and enjoy when you go home.

710
01:46:17,808 --> 01:46:24,071
But you put in a request a few years back, and I kept that special request in mind.

711
01:46:27,397 --> 01:46:40,862
I want you to know as I present you with this request, again, echoing the mayor's sentiments as well, that your contributions have been immeasurable.

712
01:46:42,923 --> 01:46:48,046
We don't want your contributions to stop, even though you are officially stepping down.

713
01:46:48,386 --> 01:46:51,787
We value you very deeply.

714
01:46:52,168 --> 01:47:06,955
And on the school side, we want you to know that we want you to continue to partner with us and provide counsel and guidance as a school committee member emeritus, as you had said to me the other day.

715
01:47:06,975 --> 01:47:11,017
But I have a special gift that you made a special request for.

716
01:47:12,085 --> 01:47:20,475
and I don't know if you recall, it says Paulette Vanderkoop, champion of our schools.

717
01:47:21,236 --> 01:47:24,700
Medford thanks you for 32 years of service.

718
01:47:46,313 --> 01:47:48,613
And so now, finally, I welcome you, Ms.

719
01:47:48,633 --> 01:47:54,795
van der Kroot, to come to the podium and share your remarks, your words with us.

720
01:47:54,875 --> 01:47:58,937
Thank you again for your dedicated service of 32 years.

721
01:48:16,173 --> 01:48:21,338
You know, it's a little bit like attending your own funeral, but you get to hear it.

722
01:48:21,478 --> 01:48:23,920
It's really great.

723
01:48:24,400 --> 01:48:28,684
I highly recommend it.

724
01:48:28,804 --> 01:48:30,045
One more citation.

725
01:48:30,706 --> 01:48:31,206
Oh, thank you.

726
01:48:31,266 --> 01:48:31,927
One more citation.

727
01:48:32,207 --> 01:48:37,312
Be proud of all the work you've done, the person you are, and the difference you have made for the past 32 years.

728
01:48:37,332 --> 01:48:38,273
Thank you so much.

729
01:48:39,293 --> 01:48:39,594
Thank you.

730
01:48:44,702 --> 01:48:48,865
Bob, we have plenty of things now to wallpaper our house with.

731
01:48:49,685 --> 01:48:54,869
First, thank you for being with me tonight, either present here in City Hall or over Zoom.

732
01:48:55,689 --> 01:49:02,234
In all my wildest dreams, I never expected to be speaking to a group of masked people or donning a mask myself.

733
01:49:03,174 --> 01:49:11,140
I am sure that over the years, especially in the earliest ones, there were times when certain people might have wished I was masked, or at least,

734
01:49:12,437 --> 01:49:22,063
a little bit less loquacious, but let's face it, the job of a school committee person rests largely on words and the ability to persuade.

735
01:49:22,904 --> 01:49:28,727
Before I go on, I want to extend a warm welcome and congratulations to my successor, Sharon Hayes.

736
01:49:29,288 --> 01:49:29,668
Sharon.

737
01:49:36,305 --> 01:49:40,690
I feel confident that you will bring your knowledge, insight, and thoughtfulness to the school committee.

738
01:49:41,070 --> 01:49:42,432
I will be cheering you on.

739
01:49:43,653 --> 01:49:54,364
Thank you to Lisa Evangelista and Susie Weiss for your work, helping me put this evening together, and also for all of the assistance you've given over the years.

740
01:49:55,553 --> 01:49:58,455
So last week, a funny thing was happening at my house.

741
01:49:59,455 --> 01:50:06,999
On two separate nights, we were awakened by our dog, Pippi, barking with great agitation.

742
01:50:07,919 --> 01:50:09,720
Something was up, including me.

743
01:50:10,581 --> 01:50:13,022
After I got her to quiet down, I heard it.

744
01:50:13,843 --> 01:50:15,123
Hoot, hoot!

745
01:50:16,184 --> 01:50:16,804
And ow!

746
01:50:17,745 --> 01:50:21,326
Over and over, it was calling, hoot, hoot!

747
01:50:23,413 --> 01:50:31,499
Now, you all know my slogan, and everybody's been reminded of it over and over, Give a Hoot the Underclute.

748
01:50:32,039 --> 01:50:35,721
And my owl appeared every two years without fail.

749
01:50:37,523 --> 01:50:40,565
But if I had any doubts last week,

750
01:50:41,760 --> 01:50:52,891
It was clear the owls had come to reclaim my owl, and it was time for my owl and me to retire and go about other owly and other things.

751
01:50:54,075 --> 01:50:56,796
I've loved this work and all the things that have gone with it.

752
01:50:57,376 --> 01:51:20,022
Being connected to so many people of Medford, working with outstanding educational leaders, relishing the accomplishments of our students, some of which you heard tonight with the musical students, interacting with our very supportive legislative leaders, being part of the larger Massachusetts Association of School Committees, meetings with my colleagues,

753
01:51:21,359 --> 01:51:25,426
many meetings with my colleagues, more meetings with my colleagues.

754
01:51:25,446 --> 01:51:28,913
I guarantee you 800 numbers is not enough.

755
01:51:31,251 --> 01:51:34,952
Last March broke the all-time record with something like 45 meetings.

756
01:51:35,772 --> 01:51:43,915
By the way, some might think that the longest meeting held was one of the marathon meetings held in this time of COVID, but it was not.

757
01:51:44,815 --> 01:51:48,296
Rather, the longest meeting I attended finished past 2 a.m.

758
01:51:48,336 --> 01:52:00,480
in the morning, a budget meeting during the time of then Special Education Director Ernie Demos, a dedicated man far more worthy than I will ever be.

759
01:52:01,690 --> 01:52:06,574
There are so many people who I've had the great opportunity to work with.

760
01:52:07,214 --> 01:52:11,757
But before I acknowledge just a few, I promised myself I would not pull a Mike McGlynn.

761
01:52:12,658 --> 01:52:20,064
See, Mayor McGlynn had the habit of making marvelous speeches, acknowledging many, and then leaving his family to the end.

762
01:52:21,004 --> 01:52:26,128
And then he would wrap up and then suddenly realize he had missed the most important people in the world, his family.

763
01:52:26,648 --> 01:52:28,069
So I'm starting with my family.

764
01:52:28,990 --> 01:52:42,678
To my dear husband, Bob, the most patient man in the world, thank you for your continued support, your work on my many campaigns, your support as I ran out the door, leaving you with, at the time, our three young kids.

765
01:52:44,003 --> 01:52:53,070
Then, thank you, fast forward, during the time of Zoom meetings for putting up with the tension that came with those meetings in our house.

766
01:52:54,111 --> 01:53:01,296
And thank you for delivering those delicious dinners that was one upside to having meetings at home by Zoom.

767
01:53:02,377 --> 01:53:06,140
Bob, you're an incredible man and incredible support, and I love you dearly.

768
01:53:07,401 --> 01:53:08,542
Thank you to my three daughters.

769
01:53:14,108 --> 01:53:18,970
Kate, Megan, and Liz, who put up with their mom being on the school committee, which was a lot.

770
01:53:19,790 --> 01:53:28,193
Phone calls during dinner, going out shopping with mom only to have her stopped by a constituent, photo shoots for campaign literature, and we'll get to that in a bit.

771
01:53:29,074 --> 01:53:35,656
I know that there was one upside in the early years when you were the very first to know about snow days.

772
01:53:37,017 --> 01:53:39,718
That doesn't happen anymore because everybody knows at once.

773
01:53:41,010 --> 01:53:44,372
Being the child of an elected official is not easy.

774
01:53:45,353 --> 01:53:54,359
I love you, my sweet daughters, and thank you for your support and for choosing such fine partners in life, Dave Ryan, Todd Prokop, and Jamie VanderKloot.

775
01:53:54,859 --> 01:54:02,264
And of course, there are my three wonderful grandsons, Harry, who is eight, Charlie, who is five, and Ezra, who is four.

776
01:54:04,290 --> 01:54:10,115
Oh, hi.

777
01:54:10,275 --> 01:54:13,197
And Megan is here, and Liz and Jamie are here.

778
01:54:13,237 --> 01:54:14,338
Todd's home with Ezra.

779
01:54:15,279 --> 01:54:16,920
And they've all been so supportive.

780
01:54:18,421 --> 01:54:22,705
I am so fortunate to have had the help and support of my friends throughout the years.

781
01:54:23,305 --> 01:54:26,108
I credit my first win to two forces in life.

782
01:54:29,222 --> 01:54:36,324
First, the very timely arrival of my daughter, Liz, who was born on my first election day.

783
01:54:37,065 --> 01:54:37,705
Thank you, Liz.

784
01:54:38,885 --> 01:54:42,987
Now, Peter, if I could ask you to turn on, will I be able to see what's up?

785
01:54:44,007 --> 01:54:46,888
Oh, this is... So the first one.

786
01:54:49,316 --> 01:54:53,620
So this is the first piece of election campaign literature I had.

787
01:54:54,020 --> 01:55:00,926
You'll notice that there's only two children in it because that's Kate and Megan, because Liz was yet to be born.

788
01:55:03,429 --> 01:55:04,570
If you could go to the next one.

789
01:55:06,732 --> 01:55:07,392
There we are.

790
01:55:07,412 --> 01:55:10,835
And she wasn't born the day before election day.

791
01:55:10,875 --> 01:55:12,317
She was born on election day.

792
01:55:13,417 --> 01:55:13,898
There we go.

793
01:55:14,378 --> 01:55:14,899
The next one.

794
01:55:16,138 --> 01:55:16,538
Let's see.

795
01:55:16,959 --> 01:55:17,879
Oh, here we are.

796
01:55:18,440 --> 01:55:20,882
And if you notice, this is the one I think that Peaches is in.

797
01:55:21,943 --> 01:55:27,508
Peaches was our first dog, and Peaches, well, frankly, more people knew Peaches than they knew me.

798
01:55:27,968 --> 01:55:38,397
Now, Mike McGlynn used to love a parade, and when we walked through the streets, Peaches would accompany us, and more people would shout out, Peaches, Peaches, than they would Paulette.

799
01:55:38,957 --> 01:55:40,959
So anyway, that's why I included that one.

800
01:55:41,259 --> 01:55:41,900
And is there one more?

801
01:55:42,760 --> 01:55:43,300
That might be it.

802
01:55:44,280 --> 01:55:52,483
Oh, and this is fast forward to 2019 with my three grandsons now there.

803
01:55:52,963 --> 01:55:58,065
So over the years, there's many more in between, but those were ones I wanted to show you tonight.

804
01:55:59,095 --> 01:56:00,256
Thank you.

805
01:56:00,877 --> 01:56:13,208
I am so fortunate to have the help and support of friends already I said that the second force was to my campaign manager, Dick O'Mara, who sadly has long left this world.

806
01:56:13,929 --> 01:56:16,851
Dick was a force of nature and a taskmaster.

807
01:56:17,652 --> 01:56:21,136
Nine months pregnant, and I was knocking on doors and giving a hoot.

808
01:56:22,177 --> 01:56:29,185
I'd like to extend my thanks to Dick's wife, Gail, and his kids, Kathleen and Brian, who were so helpful in my early years.

809
01:56:30,126 --> 01:56:37,654
And to other friends who have been so kind and supportive, in particular, my treasure and great friend, Dr. Laurie Davidson, who is with us tonight.

810
01:56:38,815 --> 01:56:48,099
And my wordsmith, David Locke, who sat with me as we painstakingly hammered out the right words for my campaign literature, and he's the photographer tonight.

811
01:56:48,939 --> 01:56:56,582
I am very fortunate to have had the blessing of my director or boss at Winchester Hospital, Marie Johnson, also here tonight.

812
01:56:57,522 --> 01:57:11,255
So when I skipped out to attend a function or run off to a meeting, and also thanks to my great co-workers Donna and Jillian, I am truly blessed to have a wide circle of loving friends and family who have always been supportive and there for me.

813
01:57:11,716 --> 01:57:12,336
Thank you all.

814
01:57:13,397 --> 01:57:17,938
I've also been extraordinarily lucky to have so many reach out and thank me when I announced my retirement.

815
01:57:18,679 --> 01:57:22,059
Many of you recounted specific times when I had been helpful to you.

816
01:57:22,580 --> 01:57:30,062
It's meant the world to me, and I thank the citizens of Medford for your thoughtfulness and support, not only recently, but over 32 years.

817
01:57:32,109 --> 01:57:39,534
As a school committee member, I had the opportunity to work with school committee members from across Massachusetts in our professional organization.

818
01:57:40,175 --> 01:57:47,780
This is a real asset to members as it enables us to understand that the challenges our community face are so often shared.

819
01:57:48,360 --> 01:57:57,447
I want to thank Glenn Kuchar and the staff of the MASC, as well as the great school committee members from across Massachusetts that I had the privilege to meet and work with.

820
01:57:58,147 --> 01:58:03,811
I'd also like to thank our legal counselor, Trinity Howard-Greenspan, who, like me, has been here forever.

821
01:58:05,032 --> 01:58:15,259
During my tenure, I've had the privilege to serve with three Medford mayors, Mike McGlynn, Stephanie Muccini-Burke, and our current mayor, Mayor Brianna Lungo-Kern.

822
01:58:16,080 --> 01:58:26,227
While there are differences among you, and after all, this is politics, some tension between you, you all have in common a deep commitment to our city.

823
01:58:27,148 --> 01:58:33,609
I am thankful that I've had the opportunity to work with all of you, and I've appreciated your leadership and devotion to Medford.

824
01:58:34,209 --> 01:58:41,351
I'd also like to mention that I think Medford is extraordinarily fortunate that our mayor serves as the head of the school committee.

825
01:58:41,911 --> 01:58:48,972
This means that our mayors have been intimately aware of the goings on in our schools and the needs of our students.

826
01:58:49,632 --> 01:58:54,733
Personally, I think this has been a giant plus, and I hope it remains this way.

827
01:58:55,803 --> 01:59:02,548
I've also had the privilege to work with a host of other school committee members over the years, some of which have graciously joined us tonight.

828
01:59:03,348 --> 01:59:06,491
Some served years and years, others for a shorter duration.

829
01:59:07,151 --> 01:59:16,738
