834
02:00:10,038 --> 02:00:15,189
and also to my current colleagues, Jenny, Kathy, Melanie, Mia, and Paul.

835
02:00:16,353 --> 02:00:23,557
Additionally, I'd like to acknowledge and once again, thank you for the work of the Building the Future Committee, led by Rick Orlando and Tricia McDonough.

836
02:00:24,038 --> 02:00:36,725
Of all the time I spent on the school committee, the period when we were deciding how to move forward with replacing our then current schools was one of the most productive and enjoyable of my tenure.

837
02:00:37,385 --> 02:00:41,208
Thank you to Tricia and Rick and all the members of the Building the Future Committee.

838
02:00:42,476 --> 02:00:44,258
Next is the really tough part.

839
02:00:44,998 --> 02:00:52,244
Acknowledging and thanking all the dedicated teachers, staff, and administrators who have dedicated their careers to our children.

840
02:00:52,904 --> 02:00:54,746
Thank you, thank you, thank you.

841
02:00:55,467 --> 02:00:58,429
I've been lucky to be in your classrooms, in our schools.

842
02:00:58,889 --> 02:01:02,552
I've attended so many events, concerts, and athletic competitions.

843
02:01:03,253 --> 02:01:06,596
I've seen our staff and teachers supporting our kids.

844
02:01:07,136 --> 02:01:11,479
And in this time of COVID, so many have just been superheroes.

845
02:01:12,320 --> 02:01:37,567
I thank each and every one, every custodian, bus driver, paraprofessional, lunch mother, school nurse, cafeteria worker, librarian, IT professional, guidance counselor, special education, administrative assistant, secretary, support staff, our dedicated afterschool staff members, staff of the Medford Family Network, Kids Corner, and of course, our teachers.

846
02:01:38,953 --> 02:01:44,114
As a school committee member, ultimately, we get to know our principals, directors, and administrative members the most.

847
02:01:44,714 --> 02:01:46,975
Thank you for all the reports you've brought to us.

848
02:01:47,315 --> 02:01:56,337
Well, maybe not those MCAS ones, because personally, I think purgatory is made of MCAS reports 24 hours a day.

849
02:01:56,357 --> 02:01:56,477
Yeah.

850
02:02:00,991 --> 02:02:10,143
Thank you for all your leadership and thank you for being patient when the latest educational acronym needs clarification yet again.

851
02:02:10,924 --> 02:02:13,467
The world of education is filled with acronyms.

852
02:02:14,418 --> 02:02:30,311
To our assistant superintendents, both past and present, and those who are here, and I'm so grateful for Beverly and Diane and all you guys up here in the front row cheering section, thank you for your countless hours of work, your patience, and your dedication.

853
02:02:31,552 --> 02:02:37,277
I've worked with three superintendents of school, Phil DeVoe, Roy Belson, and Dr. Maurice-Edouard Vincent.

854
02:02:38,148 --> 02:02:41,550
Now, the first thing I have to tell you is that nobody, Carmen, are you listening?

855
02:02:42,631 --> 02:02:45,834
Nobody, she's our intern, superintendent intern.

856
02:02:46,234 --> 02:02:48,115
And so she wants to be a superintendent.

857
02:02:48,295 --> 02:02:48,876
She's crazy.

858
02:02:51,680 --> 02:02:55,262
Now, the first thing I have to tell you is that nobody should want these jobs.

859
02:02:55,682 --> 02:02:56,362
It's tough.

860
02:02:57,142 --> 02:02:59,423
I don't know how superintendents do it, frankly.

861
02:02:59,904 --> 02:03:04,646
Everything they do, every decision they make, every conversation they have is under scrutiny.

862
02:03:05,226 --> 02:03:14,050
Seven people elected by the public who may know something about education, or maybe not so much, get to weigh in on their performance all the time.

863
02:03:14,770 --> 02:03:15,370
Good grief.

864
02:03:15,931 --> 02:03:17,652
They are on call 24-7.

865
02:03:18,172 --> 02:03:25,337
They have to become experts on everything, including weather, and whether there is going to be enough snow to justify calling off school.

866
02:03:26,458 --> 02:03:33,362
Thank you, Roy, for devoting 50 years of your life to the Medford Public Schools and for leading this district, for 23 of them.

867
02:03:33,842 --> 02:03:43,409
You started and guided so many great programs that are shining stars for Medford, including the Medford Family Network and the Center for Citizenship and Social Responsibility.

868
02:03:44,209 --> 02:03:47,010
And Maurice, thank you for stepping in and stepping up.

869
02:03:47,590 --> 02:03:50,851
Your leadership since the beginning of COVID has been very strong.

870
02:03:51,331 --> 02:03:54,592
You worked to get our students back in school at the earliest opportunity.

871
02:03:55,032 --> 02:04:04,434
Your guiding principles of ACE, achievement for all, collaboration for all, and equity for all, have guided your work and set the vision for our district.

872
02:04:04,914 --> 02:04:07,335
Dr. Edward Vincent, keep on going.

873
02:04:08,255 --> 02:04:11,777
It takes a long time to thank a lot of people that you've worked with for 32 years.

874
02:04:12,338 --> 02:04:13,759
Thank you for your kind indulgence.

875
02:04:14,619 --> 02:04:16,701
In leaving, I have two words of wisdom.

876
02:04:17,181 --> 02:04:18,182
Well, let's say thoughts.

877
02:04:19,456 --> 02:04:31,825
For my colleagues, the toughest time I've ever spent on the committee was when we had to lay off teachers and staff who were truly valuable, but because of a national economic crisis, we could not sustain.

878
02:04:32,706 --> 02:04:41,853
As you spend the ESSER money, please take to heart the need to spend wisely so that in some future date, you are not facing a dire situation.

879
02:04:42,513 --> 02:04:46,556
Yes, spend it for sure, but plan so that you put into place

880
02:04:47,397 --> 02:04:51,240
but plan so that what you put into place can be maintained for the future.

881
02:04:51,820 --> 02:04:53,441
It's going to be a huge challenge.

882
02:04:54,382 --> 02:04:58,284
And lastly, this period in our community and in our nation has been tough.

883
02:04:59,085 --> 02:05:01,266
The divisiveness has truly been heartbreaking.

884
02:05:01,907 --> 02:05:13,915
While we cannot snap our fingers and fix the entire national divide, it is incumbent on every local elected official and each of us to listen to and work with all of our fellow citizens and constituents.

885
02:05:14,615 --> 02:05:16,136
Let's find a way to build bridges.

886
02:05:17,237 --> 02:05:18,898
We have the best students in Medford.

887
02:05:19,398 --> 02:05:20,999
They have so much hope and promise.

888
02:05:21,159 --> 02:05:22,599
You heard some of them tonight.

889
02:05:23,459 --> 02:05:30,362
I thank them and I thank all of you for your extraordinary opportunity I have had in being a member of the Medford School Committee.

890
02:05:31,302 --> 02:05:37,765
Now I'm going to finish with an inside joke, which some of you will understand and many of you won't, but

891
02:05:39,186 --> 02:05:48,213
In honor of the late former athletic director, Bud Kelly, I have blue and white running through my veins.

892
02:05:49,394 --> 02:05:50,975
